      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid project car with good bones and a surprisingly eager drivetrain. Starts, runs, and moves, with a powertrain that feels willing and a chassis that still has plenty of life for someone who knows what they\u2019re looking at. Not a showpiece, but a great candidate for a budget build, commuter revival, or parts-plus-platform setup. Recent maintenance attention helps, and it\u2019s being offered as an honest, usable driver that can be improved while enjoyed. If you want an affordable entry point with real potential, this one makes a strong case.",
